text: Masovian Voivodeship is one of the 16 Voivodeships of Poland. It can be found in the east-central part of Poland. It is mostly in the historical land of Masovia. The capital of the Voivodeship is Warsaw. The province was created on January 1, 1999. Kampinos National Park is in the province. Category:1999 establishments in Poland
title: Masovian Voivodeship
